A tragic construction accident occurred in Manhattan when a crane collapsed, killing at least four people and injuring many.
Residents had previously complained about unsafe working conditions and the rapid pace of construction.
The crane, mounted on a skyscraper, toppled and smashed into residential buildings, causing devastation.
Rescue efforts continued throughout the night to find survivors in the rubble.
The incident highlighted the dangers posed by construction cranes in urban areas and raised questions about safety measures and regulations.
The community mourned the loss of lives and prayed for the victims and their families.
